{
  "texts": [
    "A structured roadmap tailored to resource-constrained environments can enable scalable implementation of ESG-AI platforms.",
    "Figure 5 outlines a five-phase pathway from readiness assessment to full-scale deployment.The first phase involves an internal audit of ESG data assets, maturity levels, and materiality drivers.",
    "SMEs should map available data to reporting frameworks and identify priority use cases-such as carbon tracking or social compliance alerts [38].",
    "This is followed by a pilot deployment phase using low-code AI tools or third-party platforms to test ESG automation for specific disclosures.In the third phase, feedback loops are embedded to evaluate performance, model fairness, and data coverage.",
    "Tools like AutoML simplify algorithm selection and tuning, while open-source ESG taxonomies help align with global standards [39]."
  ]
}